responses.response_1:
Member Lookup and Information Commands

`[w!i or w!whois]` + `<username>` (internal) or `<user id>` (external).

You don't have to type the full thing if you are sure it's the only member with a username/tag/ID that starts with what you want to provide.

For example, I know that Mobilfan#1234 is the only member with such a name, I can just do w!i mobil and Wick would pick it up.

Example Use Case: `w!i @Drew` or `w!i 671403408900489238`
responses.response_2:
Role Lookup and Information Commands

`[w!i or w!info]` + `<role name>` or `<role id>`

Example Use Case: `w!info @Community Staff` or `w!info 745716280715378859`
responses.response_4:
Moderation Case Information Commands`

[w!cases]`

Optionally you can specify individual cases by adding `<case-id>/<user> <parameters>`

Example Use Case: `w!cases 123 ?e ?off`
responses.response_5:
Moderation Case Accepted Parameters

`[w!cases <caseid/user> <parameter>]

`Parameters include:

Edit a case: `[?e]`
Set new case reason: `[?r <new reason>]`
Close a case: `[?off/clearcase]`
Re-open a case: `[?on]`
Show a list of cases by type: `[?t type]`
View quarantines: `[q]`
View unquarantines: `[uq]`

Example Use Case: `w!cases @Drew ?e ?r best admin ;)`
responses.response_6:
Moderation Case Accepted Types

`[w!cases ?t <type>`

Types include:

View ban cases: `[Bans/B]`
View unban cases: `[Unbans/UB]`
View kick cases: `[Kicks/K]`
View mute cases: `[Mutes/M]`
View unmute cases: `[Unmutes/UM]`
View quarantine cases: `[Quarantines/Q]`
View unquarantine cases: `[Unquarantines/UQ]`

Example Use Case: `w!cases @Drew ?t mutes`
responses.response_7:
Moderation - Warning Users

`[w!wa]` + `<username/id>` + `[<?r>] <reason>` (optional)

Accepted Parameters for Warning Users:

Add a reason: `[<?r>] <reason>`

Example Use Case: `w!warn @Drew ?r best admin ;)`
responses.response_8:
Moderation - Muting/Unmuting Users

`[w!m/mute]` or `[w!um/unmute]` + `<username/id>` + `[<?r>] <reason>` (optional)

Accepted Parameters for Muting/Unmuting Users:

Add a reason: `<?r> <reason>`

DM the user: `[<?dm>]`

Add duration to mute: `[?t <time>]`

Mute users not in server: `[?h]`

Send compact response: `<?p>`

Example Use Case: `w!m @Drew ?t 24h ?r best admin ;)`
responses.response_9:
Moderation - Purging User Messages

`[w!p]` or `[w!c]` or `[w!sleep]` or `[w!clear]` + `<no. of messages>` + `<user/parameter>` (optional)

Accepted Paramaters for purging messages:
Target suspicious users messages: `[s]`
Target bot messages: `[b]`
Target non bot messages: `[u]`
Target webhook messages: `[w]`
Target messages by users w/ no pfp: `[noav]`

Target messages sent by users with no role: `[nr]`

Target embedded messages: `[e]`

Target attachment messages: `[a]`

Target links: `[l]`

Target messages from specific roles: `[members]`

Target messages with reactions: `[reactions]`

Target messages that contain emojis: `[emojis]`

Target messages with text only: `[text]`

Example use case: `w!p 50 -b`
responses.response_10:
Moderation - Kicking Users

`[w!kick]` or `[w!k]` + `<parameters>`

Accepted Parameters for kicking users:

Add a reason: `[?r] <reason>`
DM the user: `[?dm]`
Send compact response: `[?p]`

Example use case: `w!k @Drew ?r worst admin :(`
responses.response_11:
Moderation - Banning/Unbanning Users

`[w!b/ban]` or `[w!ub/unban]` + `<parameters>`

Accepted Parameters for Banning/Unbanning users:

 Add a reason: `[?r] <reason>`
DM the user: `[dm]`
Add duration to ban: `[?t] <time>`
Ban users NOT in the server: `[?h] <USERID_ONLY>`
Send compact response: `[?p]`
Soft ban the user: `[?soft/s]

Example Use Case: `w!ban @Drew ?r haha, you're banned!`

If you want to permenantly ban a user that you KNOW is in the server, use the `[w!b]` (reg. ban) command.

If you want to ban a user that is NOT in the server, use the `[w!h]` (hackban) command

If you want to ban a user and immediatley unban the user, use the `[?s]` (softban) command.
responses.response_12:
Moderation - Quarantine/Unquarantine Users

`[w!q]` or `[w!uq/restore/r]`

Accepted Parameters for Quarantining/Unquaranting Users:

`[?r] <reason>`

Example Use Case: `w!quarantine @Drew ?r too nice`
